{
  "texts": [
    "For a secret s ∈ R q that is chosen according to χ s, the RLWE distribution samples a ∈ R q uniformly, samples an error e ∈ R q according to χ e, computes b:= as + e ∈ R q, and outputs (a, b).",
    "Definition 5 (Decision RLWE).",
    "The Decision RLWE problem asks to decide whether samples (a, b) are from the RLWE distribution or are chosen uniformly at random from R q × R q.",
    "Definition 6 (Search RLWE).",
    "The Search RLWE problem asks to recover s given m samples {(a i, b i = a i • s + e i): i = 1,."
  ]
}